cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the automated segmentation of plant roots from minirhizotron imagery using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of supervised learning techniques and deep neural networks for this task also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained features and transfer learning, which are common techniques in both computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the sub-categories cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) are also likely candidates.
